      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 4 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Built on Yesterday."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Side Effect Oracle showed you one drug's FDA adverse event profile. Side Effect Storm loads up to three drugs simultaneously, overlays their adverse reaction profiles on a D3 spider chart, animates 24 months of reporting trends, fires Claude extended thinking to reason about dangerous combination risks — and then rates the whole combination on an animated storm-severity gauge, from LIGHT DRIZZLE to CATEGORY 4 HURRICANE."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com/p/summer-into-ai-eric-week3-submission-12d",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Eric's Emission Factors (Week 3)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " took a dry federal dataset and made it explorable. Side Effect Storm does the same with FDA FAERS — but makes multi-drug comparison the core mechanic, so the AI surfaces combination risks that no single-drug view can show"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Parallel FDA FAERS fetches"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — for each drug, the API fetches top 15 adverse reactions, a seriousness breakdown, 24 months of monthly event counts, and label warning text — all in parallel via Promise.all."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "D3 radar chart comparison"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — the union of all three drugs' top-10 reactions becomes the spider chart axes. Each drug gets a colored polygon. Shared reactions where one drug dominates are immediately visible."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Claude extended thinking for interactions"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — with 2+ drugs loaded, Claude receives all full data profiles and uses 8,000 thinking tokens to identify dangerous combinations, shared risk factors, and vulnerable populations. The reasoning streams live."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "The storm gauge — structured AI output driving the UI"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — after the prose analysis, a second forced tool call distills everything into { riskLevel 1-10, stormCategory, headline, keyInteraction }. The UI renders it as an animated severity bar. Ambien + Xanax scores a 9/10 CATEGORY 4 HURRICANE with the specific fatal interaction named. The AI's judgment becomes interface state, not just text."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enter up to three drug names (or click a quick-pick chip like 'Lipitor + Metformin')."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Click ANALYZE DATA to load the spider chart, severity bars, and trend sparklines."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "With two or more drugs loaded, click "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "ANALYZE COMBINATION"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to stream Claude's extended thinking interaction analysis."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "STORM SEVERITY"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " gauge fill when the analysis completes. Try notorious combos: Ambien + Xanax, Warfarin + Aspirin + Ibuprofen."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
